Elvira Popescu https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Elvira_Popescu 0 Elvira Popescu (Romanian pronunciation: [elˈvira poˈpesku]; in French, Elvire Popesco; 10 May 1894 – 11 December 1993) was a Romanian-French stage and movie actress and theatre director. During the 1930s and 1940s she starred in a number of French comedy films.
